@srkukarni I think the existing:

@Override
   public KVStreamlet<KeyedWindow<K>, V>
       reduceByKeyAndWindow(WindowConfig windowCfg, SerializableBinaryOperator<V> reduceFn) 

should be called by the more generic version with the identity parameter.  The identity parameter can just be passed as null or something.  This way you don't have two implementations of the same thing essentially

@srkukarni Now that I think about it, it seems like it'd be better to just use the `consume` operator for this. Like so:

```java
builder.newKVSource(() -> new KeyValue<>("player1", 1234))
        .consume(s -> LOG.info(/* formatted string */));
```

I don't think that providing a new operator is much of a win. Happy to close this if you agree.

@jerrypeng Thanks for your comments. 
First, I agree that the way ports are currently managed is error prone. Thanks for taking this up.
However, this PR is addressing some future needs and I don't understand them well. Personally I find this solution overfitting. I think it would be better for one more reviewer to take a look.
